 (144, 1, '2018-08-23 19:54:27', '2018-08-23 19:54:27', 'You have a petition with signatures. AWESOME. Now what? Here are some critical reminders and instructions:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please return the petition(s) <strong>as soon as possible</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>This is a legal document, so <strong>don\'t copy or cut</strong> it up. We need the original, entire document.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Fill in the back</strong> of any completed petition. Unfold it and look for the <strong>Petition Gatherer</strong>section at the bottom.</li>\r\n 	<li>Don\'t use the petition itself as an envelope. It must be <strong>mailed in a separate envelope</strong>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Email <a href="mailto:petitions@wholewashington.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">petitions@wholewashington.org</a> Let us know how many signatures you’re sending.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThen to return it, you have 3 options:\r\n<h3>1. MAIL BY JUNE 30th!</h3>\r\nSend to: <strong>P.O. Box 768 Bothell, WA 98041</strong> (U.S. Postal Service only)\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A 9 x 12 envelope can fit up to 5 petitions folded in half.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>One petition will cost about $1.50 in postage.</li>\r\n 	<li>Five petitions will cost about $3.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Flat rate mailers are also available at the post office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>2. MAKE ARRANGEMENTS</h3>\r\nEmail us at <a href="mailto:petitions@wholewashington.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">petitions@wholewashington.org</a> with your location. We\'ll try to make pick up/drop off arrangements with a Volunteer close to you.\r\n<h3>3. DROP OFF (and/or PICK UP NEW)</h3>\r\nUse the map below for to find locations. ↓\r\n<h4>Thanks for your support. We couldn’t do this without you!</h4>', 'Return or Pick Up Petitions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'return-or-pick-up-petitions', '', '', '2018-08-23 19:54:27', '2018-08-23 19:54:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?page_id=144', 0, 'page', '', 0),
